371.title: Definition of Done
371.abstract: The Definition of Done (DoD) is not only a checklist that has to be executed to get a piece of work delivered. The DoD and the path to its determination opens a space for agile thinking and acting which can actively be leveraged by the delivery team and the surrounding organization. It is a great entry point for agile delivery, and it can be used in Scrum, Kanban or any other procedure with iterated delivery.

372.title: Scrum and Architecture
372.abstract: Cooperatively making architecture decisions, at a point in time when they are needed, and not earlier, is a quality-improving paradigm in agile software development. Conceptual integrity in the flow of architecture decisions will only be achieved if one person has the final word regarding those decisions. This is the architect, whose rights and obligations in the context of the Scrum process are being reflected in this essay.
